{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"ff_federal_dependency_by_year","neutral_annotation":"Federal transfers (INTERGOVERNMENTAL REVENUE/FEDERAL) as share of total revenue. ~41% pre-2020, peaked 48.0% in FY2023, 45.5% in FY2025 — above the pre-pandemic baseline. FY2022 absent from source data."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"ff_federal_dependency_by_agency_year","neutral_annotation":"Per-agency federal revenue share. Concentrated in AHCCCS (Medicaid, ~81% of $20.4B), Economic Security (~97%), Emergency & Military Affairs (~95%)."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"pf_duplicate_payment_groups","neutral_annotation":"Same vendor_id+reference_id+amount across distinct transaction_ids on different days. Different-day exposure $706.9M, of which 99.1% is Medicaid managed-care capitation (multi-cycle payment mechanics); non-Medicaid reviewable residual is $6.3M (largest single item $9,981). Confirmation requires warrant-number reconciliation not present in source data."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"pf_structuring_by_agency","neutral_annotation":"Ratio of expenditures just under $5,000 (4,750-4,999.99) to just over. Elevated for Dept of Veterans Services (1.77), Senate (1.57), House (1.32); their $10k ratios are <1. Consistent with a $5k small-purchase threshold; not evidence of intent."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"pf_vendor_concentration","neutral_annotation":"Largest single external vendor as share of an agency's expenditures (self/internal payments excluded). Indicates sole-source/dependency exposure, not irregularity."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"pf_vendor_compliance","neutral_annotation":"Vendors screened against live OFAC SDN (19,050 entries, normalized exact-name) and Section 889 / FAR-4.20 prohibited sources (word-boundary token match). 127,858 vendors / $277B screened. List-based and reproducible; a hit is a name match warranting confirmation, not proof of a prohibited transaction. Substring matching was rejected after it produced 25 false positives ($47M, all \"Aztec\"-named AZ firms vs token ZTE)."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"gov_scorecard","neutral_annotation":"Net-cash-margin is a checkbook cash-basis proxy, NOT GAAP. AG-audited ACFR shows State net position INCREASED $259M in FY2024 despite our -3.2% cash reading (~$2.2B cash-vs-accrual divergence); FY2024 \"watch\" is a timing/liquidity signal, not accrual deterioration. ACFR governs."}}
{"feed":"feed_annotations","row":{"metric":"ag_findings_xref","neutral_annotation":"Cross-reference of our data-derived signals to AZ Auditor General FY2024 Single Audit findings. Independent corroboration: our transaction analysis surfaced the same AHCCCS/DES risk concentration the AG flagged by audit. One CORRECTS row where audited accrual data overrides our cash proxy."}}
